quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,30,"On the Day that each self finds the good it did, and the evil it did, present there in front of it, it will wish there were an age between it and then. Allah advises you to beware of Him. Allah is Ever-Gentle with His slaves"
  3,31,"Say, ´If you love Allah, then follow me and Allah will love you and forgive you for your wrong actions. Allah is Ever-Forgiving, Most Merciful.´"
  3,32,"Say, ´Obey Allah and the Messenger.´ Then if they turn away, Allah does not love the kafirun"
  3,33,Allah chose Adam and Nuh and the family of Ibrahim and the family of ´Imran over all other beings —
  3,34,"descendants one of the other. Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,35,"Remember when the wife of ´Imran said, ´My Lord, I have pledged to You what is in my womb, devoting it to Your service. Please accept my prayer. You are the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing.´"
  3,36,"When she gave birth, she said, ´My Lord! I have given birth to a girl´ — and Allah knew very well what she had given birth to, male and female are not the same — ´and I have named her Maryam and placed her and her children in Your safekeeping from the accursed Shaytan.´"
  3,37,"Her Lord accepted her with approval and made her grow in health and beauty. And Zakariyya became her guardian. Every time Zakariyya visited her in the Upper Room, he found food with her. He said, ´Maryam, how did you come by this?´ She said, ´It is from Allah. Allah provides for whoever He wills without any reckoning.´"